            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div class="border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary mb-2">How much does a master bathroom remodel cost in Seattle?</h3>
                <p class="text-body-text text-sm leading-relaxed">Mid-range: $25,000-$40,000. High-end: $50,000-$100,000+. A basic refresh costs $5,000-$10,000. Labor accounts for about 40-50% of total cost in the Seattle market.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary mb-2">How long does a master bathroom remodel take?</h3>
                <p class="text-body-text text-sm leading-relaxed">4-8 weeks for construction. Add 4-12 weeks for Seattle permits if needed. Simple updates take 1-2 weeks. Total planning-to-completion timeline is typically 3-5 months.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Do I need a permit for a bathroom remodel in Seattle?</h3>
                <p class="text-body-text text-sm leading-relaxed">Cosmetic updates (paint, hardware, accessories) do not require permits. Plumbing relocation, electrical changes, and structural modifications do require SDCI permits. Like-for-like fixture swaps usually do not.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary mb-2">What is the best order for a bathroom remodel?</h3>
                <p class="text-body-text text-sm leading-relaxed">Demo, rough plumbing/electrical, structural work, waterproofing, tile, vanity/countertop, toilet, fixture trim, glass shower door, paint/trim, final cleaning and inspection.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Should I remodel my master bathroom before selling?</h3>
                <p class="text-body-text text-sm leading-relaxed">A dated master bath can hurt your sale. A mid-range remodel ($25,000-$40,000) typically recoups 60-70% at resale while making the home more attractive. Focus on neutral finishes that appeal broadly.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>


